This was probably the most bland spaghetti I’ve ever had. It just wasn’t good. It was close to the convention center so the location is convenient. The line snaked in the restaurant around the dining tables. I’m not sure I’d want to eat here. Too many distractions with people standing, talking, and moving while I’m trying to eat. They ran out of salad and had only pasta salad at 11am. Bags are 5 cents but I wasn’t asked if I wanted one. I’m a frugal person so having the option to save should have been offered. The pizza looked pretty good.

Ok so I found that if I joined the Sbarro Society and I purchased a drink at the Sbarro that I was able to get a free XL slice of Pizza. Turns out that "this location is a franchise and only corporate locations do that...... I mean we just don't do it..... yeah we don't that" is the dialogue I received when trying to redeem my coupon in which they never looked at. Well in the Society now so I guess they will let me in on which locations actually take the coupon. They were rude actually pretty mild tempered and relax but they were very sort with me. It did rub me the wrong way that the employee were sitting eating pizza .... probably a free slice 😡

Ideally located one block from the Mount Vernon Square Metro station,  4 blocks north of Chinatown, and on a main bus route is this busy location. They are also attached to the Washington Convention Center and a favorite for attendees, local businesses and tourists.  For their location,  they could benefit from a larger location and outdoor seating. There is no parking, so be prepared to find parking nearby and walk.  The serice is quick,  seating is limited and the food is good. Great for a quick bite. Plus the prices are reasonable.
